title: Frederick Douglass National Historic Site: History & Culture
body: Explore This Park    Learn About the Park     History & Culture             History & Culture             Frederick Douglass   Frederick Douglass was a runaway slave, abolitionist, equal rights advocate, and statesman.            Cedar Hill   Cedar Hill was the name of Frederick Douglass's estate in Anacostia.        Collections   The site cares for thousands of original objects that belonged to the Douglasses.        Preservation    The historic house and landscape have been protected for more than a hundred years.
